The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which is a well-known computer vision problem falling under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves sparse dictionary learning, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves extensive experiments and evaluation of the proposed method, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves the use of transfer learning, which is a common technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves the use of sparse features encoding, which is a technique commonly used in cryptography (cs.CR).
